
[1]vilify

   VIL'IFY, v.t. [from vile.]

   1. To make vile; to debase; to degrade.

   Their Maker's image forsook them, when themselves they vilified to
   serve ungovern'd appetite.

   2. To defame; to traduce; to attempt to degrade by slander.

   Many passions dispose us to depress and vilify the merit of one rising
   in the esteem of mankind.

   [This is the most usual sense of the verb.]
